ANTHRAX, BOVINE - INDIA: (WEST BENGAL)
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Tue 5 Feb 2008
Source: Ananda Bazar Patrika [in Hindi, trans. submitter, edited]
<http://www.anandabazar.com>
Published: 5th February, 2008


A total of 14 cows died in 3 villages of Mathabhanga area in the
district of Cooch Behar in West Bengal, India. Laboratory tests of
their blood samples revealed anthrax bacilli. District magistrate of
Cooch Behar Mr Rajash Singh announced that all cows in the locality
will be vaccinated. However, he did not impose any restriction of any
intake of milk and beef in the locality.

--
